NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENT_URL=http://localhost:8765

Web login uses local agent session tokens stored at runtime.
Legacy NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENT_TOKEN is intentionally not used by the login UI.

Server-side local agent only. Put these in ../.env.local or the FastAPI
process environment before starting scripts/run_agent.py, scripts/start_local.ps1,
or the desktop "Mo Web" launcher. Do not expose DEEPSEEK_API_KEY as NEXT_PUBLIC_*.
TRASH_SORTER_AUTH_DEV_DEFAULTS=1
TRASH_SORTER_AUTH_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://trash_user:strong-password@localhost:5432/trash_sorter
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://trash_user:strong-password@localhost:5432/trash_sorter
TRASH_SORTER_AUTH_DB=
TRASH_SORTER_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_USERNAME=owner
TRASH_SORTER_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me-before-production
TRASH_SORTER_SESSION_HOURS=12
TRASH_SORTER_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-api-key-here
DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com
# Backend locks DeepSeek to deepseek-v4-flash. Keep this value for test compatibility.
DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
DEEPSEEK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=75
